article.description: — Dimigus Stevens hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer and MJ Randolph registered 17 points, eight rebounds and six assists as Florida A&M narrowly beat Prairie View 61-60 on Monday night.
article.headline: Stevens' buzzer-beater lifts Florida A&M past Prairie View
article.linkText: Stevens' buzzer-beater lifts Florida A&M past Prairie View
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- — Dimigus Stevens hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer and MJ Randolph registered 17 points, eight rebounds and six assists as Florida A&M narrowly beat Prairie View 61-60 on Monday night. Stevens had 12 points for Florida A&M (10-12, 8-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Keith Littles added 11 points. DJ Jones had 11 rebounds and four blocks. Markedric Bell had 13 points and seven rebounds for the Panthers (4-15, 4-5). Jeremiah Gambrell, Jr. added 10 points. DeWayne Cox had six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
